feat(profile): add change password functionality

Implement the ability for both teachers and students to change their own passwords on their respective profile pages.

Key changes include:
- Adding a "Change Password" form to the profile views.
- Implementing the API call to `PUT /api/users/me/password`.
- Translating API error messages into user-friendly Chinese.
- Making password fields visible by default for ease of use in a teaching context.

fix(auth): prevent logout on incorrect password entry

Modify the global API client to ignore 401 errors specifically from the password change endpoint. This prevents the user from being logged out when they enter an invalid current password.

fix(ui): improve profile and sidebar UX

- Correct color inconsistencies on the Question Bank page.
- Ensure the sidebar menu remains expanded after a page refresh.
- Adjust the layout of profile page sections for better logical flow.
